Hi,

Make sure the heritrix user can write to the state  folder and if you have
files in the state folder delete them.



From: archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com
[mailto:archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of Jian
Sent: Friday, April 26, 2013 6:04 AM
To: archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [archive-crawler] Unable to setup bdb environment - jobs directory
set to an NFS drive





I am crawling with Heritrix 1.14.4, which is installed in a local drive.
When I use the default settings, everything went well. However, I found that
the local drive is not big enough so I mounted an external drive in NFS type
and change the &quot;heritrix.jobsdir&quot; to a directory in the NFS mounted drive.
This causes a problem as the crawler does not crawl. In &quot;state.job&quot; file, it
reports that 

&quot;A fatal InitializationException occured when loading job:
On crawl: crawltest Unable to setup bdb environment.&quot;

I should say that heritrix should have writing permission to this folder
because the &quot;logs&quot; &quot;scratch&quot; and &quot;checkpoints&quot; folders are all created and
&quot;order.xml&quot; file is there, too. 

I read some posts before and kind of get an impression that this error may
be caused by using an NFS mounted drive. But how to get around it? Please
help.




